WEBVTT

00:47.384 --> 00:48.950
What lens are you on?

00:48.984 --> 00:50.284
Can we get a camera
set up over here?

00:50.317 --> 00:52.384
Thank you, Janine. I'm here at
the New York County Courthouse,

00:52.417 --> 00:55.750
waiting for Lauren Monroe to
give a statement to the press.

01:00.417 --> 01:02.251
Sir, one moment, please.

01:04.417 --> 01:06.717
Set it up over there.
I'll be right there.

01:20.050 --> 01:21.917
Make sure we have full access
to the SEC filings.

01:21.950 --> 01:24.783
Let's get updated lists of
shell companies ASAP as well.

01:24.817 --> 01:26.251
And keep having everyone
comb for discrepancies

01:26.284 --> 01:27.451
in the shareholder reports.

01:27.484 --> 01:28.917
I need a meeting
with Haeven at 2:00.

01:30.884 --> 01:32.984
Please! I can't answer
all your questions at once!

01:33.017 --> 01:35.151
Okay, one at a time.
Katie, go ahead.

01:40.451 --> 01:41.518
What do you say
to those who think

01:41.551 --> 01:44.251
that Wall Street has corrupted
the justice system?

01:44.284 --> 01:46.351
Well, after my first year
as district attorney,

01:46.384 --> 01:48.217
I'd say that my conviction rate
speaks for itself.

01:48.251 --> 01:50.717
Victims and their families have
always been my only concern,

01:50.750 --> 01:52.217
not bankers and brokers.

01:57.351 --> 01:58.950
Beautiful morning,
isn't it, Lauren?

01:58.984 --> 02:00.884
Save your bullshit for the jury.

02:00.917 --> 02:03.950
- It's time we talk plea deal.
- We did. I turned it down.

02:03.984 --> 02:05.884
Is it true that
Thomas Reindorff's legal team

02:05.917 --> 02:07.217
reached out with a plea deal?

02:07.251 --> 02:08.917
A plea deal
without restitution

02:08.949 --> 02:10.883
for the $3.5 billion dollars
he defrauded investors

02:10.917 --> 02:12.783
is no plea deal
I would ever accept.

02:15.717 --> 02:17.683
There's no way
you can prove my client

02:17.717 --> 02:19.750
was aware of
or condoned the actions

02:19.783 --> 02:21.750
- of a few rogue traitors.
- Watch me.

02:21.783 --> 02:23.251
You can rest assured
they'll face their own day

02:23.284 --> 02:25.084
in court for collusion.

02:25.117 --> 02:27.184
Ladies and gentlemen,
please put your hands together

02:27.217 --> 02:29.750
for District Attorney
Lauren Monroe!

02:29.783 --> 02:31.717
Your brother's running
for reelection to Congress

02:31.750 --> 02:33.050
with less than ten days to go.

02:33.084 --> 02:34.317
A conviction would be
very convenient

02:34.351 --> 02:35.950
in helping the family image.

02:35.984 --> 02:37.850
Thank you, thank you.

02:37.884 --> 02:41.384
My brother has one thing
no other opponent does:

02:41.417 --> 02:42.850
tenacity.

02:42.884 --> 02:45.117
Ladies and gentlemen,
my brother,

02:45.151 --> 02:47.084
Congressman William Monroe.

02:47.117 --> 02:49.151
And as far as my brother's
reelection campaign goes,

02:49.184 --> 02:51.683
I'm sure he'd donate blood
in exchange for your vote.

02:53.184 --> 02:55.417
Speaking of the election,
is there any credence

02:55.451 --> 02:57.151
to the New York Post article
that claims your brother

02:57.184 --> 02:58.917
traded favors
in exchange for union support?

02:58.950 --> 03:00.317
Absolutely not.

03:00.351 --> 03:02.151
Desperation
looks good on you, Robert.

03:02.184 --> 03:05.251
Your father would've
told you to take the deal.

03:05.284 --> 03:07.683
Your client
is a sociopathic liar

03:07.717 --> 03:09.917
that defrauded people of
their pensions and life savings.

03:13.484 --> 03:15.917
We're just now getting in word
about your father's accident.

03:15.950 --> 03:17.850
I...

03:17.884 --> 03:20.417
We just received notice
that he was found dead

03:20.451 --> 03:22.917
at your family's summer house.

03:22.950 --> 03:25.417
Can you please comment on your
father's death, Miss Monroe?

03:25.451 --> 03:28.251
Thank you. It's an incredible
honor to be here with you.

03:28.284 --> 03:29.417
Lauren!

03:31.984 --> 03:33.950
One statement about your father!

03:36.317 --> 03:37.884
That'll be all for now.
That's enough!

03:41.017 --> 03:42.850
Jackie, get them out of here!

04:32.417 --> 04:35.984
Earth to earth,
ashes to ashes, dust to dust.

05:13.417 --> 05:16.151
Hey, take care, okay?

05:19.284 --> 05:22.717
Hey, listen, I gotta be back
at the station at 4:00,

05:22.750 --> 05:25.351
but I'm sorry
for your loss, Lauren.

05:27.717 --> 05:30.117
Thanks for all your help,
Emilio.

05:30.151 --> 05:32.117
- Take care, okay?
- Thanks.

05:46.017 --> 05:48.151
You're better at this
than I am.

05:48.184 --> 05:50.950
Well, I had plenty of practice.
You just nod and shake hands.

05:52.984 --> 05:55.317
A heart attack.

05:55.351 --> 05:57.750
I mean, how'd that even happen?

05:57.783 --> 06:01.351
Dad was in better shape
than either of us.

06:01.384 --> 06:03.884
What are we gonna do
about Mom?

06:03.917 --> 06:06.117
Just surround her with friends,

06:06.151 --> 06:09.251
And we'll find her an apartment
on Zillow, closer to us.

06:11.151 --> 06:14.783
Look, I can only stay
until the reading of the will.

06:14.817 --> 06:16.917
Campaign's a circus.

06:19.950 --> 06:22.950
Hey, Dad was proud of you.

06:24.451 --> 06:27.017
Maybe in public,

06:27.050 --> 06:29.717
but we both know
you were the golden child.

06:34.950 --> 06:38.251
Can't believe
it's already been a week.

06:38.284 --> 06:40.683
It's the beginning of the end.

07:44.783 --> 07:47.050
I know how
to play the game.

07:47.084 --> 07:49.317
This game, like life,
requires forethought.

07:49.351 --> 07:51.717
It's not about where you are.

07:51.750 --> 07:54.817
It's where you'll be
in ten moves or ten years.

07:56.184 --> 07:58.850
You are not allowed
to be average.

07:58.884 --> 08:00.417
We all have to put up with
things that we don't like,

08:00.451 --> 08:04.017
so grow up, pick a firm,
and learn how to win.

08:04.050 --> 08:05.284
Checkmate.

08:07.451 --> 08:11.451
"I leave Catherine in sole
control of the family estate

08:11.484 --> 08:14.884
and my voting rights
on the board of directors.

08:14.917 --> 08:17.950
To my son, William,

08:17.984 --> 08:22.217
I leave the sum
of $20 million.

08:22.251 --> 08:26.317
To Lauren, I leave $1 million.

08:26.351 --> 08:29.217
$50 million is to be split

08:29.251 --> 08:34.116
equally between the Police
and Firemen's Benevolent Fund

08:34.150 --> 08:36.150
and the Harvard School
of Medicine.

08:36.183 --> 08:39.150
This is my Last Will
and Testament.

08:39.183 --> 08:40.384
Archer Monroe."

08:40.417 --> 08:42.984
Thank you, Harold.
That'll be all.

08:45.251 --> 08:46.717
I need some air.

08:46.750 --> 08:49.017
Thank you, Harold.

08:52.117 --> 08:55.050
Thank you for everything
you've done for us, Harold.

08:55.084 --> 08:57.117
I know that
you and my dad were close.

09:00.050 --> 09:02.817
There's actually...

09:02.850 --> 09:06.317
something I need
to discuss with you.

09:06.351 --> 09:10.850
Your father left this
for you and you alone.

09:12.251 --> 09:16.084
I knew your father
for 31 years, Lauren.

09:16.117 --> 09:20.084
He was proud of
the woman you became.

09:20.117 --> 09:23.717
Don't let the inheritance
speak otherwise.

09:25.384 --> 09:26.884
Thank you.

10:00.750 --> 10:02.117
Okay.

10:07.050 --> 10:10.317
Lauren, it pains me to do this,

10:10.351 --> 10:12.417
and if you have received this,

10:12.451 --> 10:14.417
it means that I never
found the courage

10:14.451 --> 10:18.783
to tell you
while I was alive or...

10:18.817 --> 10:21.084
I died before
I handled it myself.

10:21.117 --> 10:22.850
And for that...

10:25.783 --> 10:27.950
for many things...

10:29.084 --> 10:30.451
forgive me.

10:30.484 --> 10:32.850
We've all made mistakes.

10:32.884 --> 10:36.151
This was mine.

10:36.184 --> 10:39.251
It is a secret you must
carry to your grave.

10:39.284 --> 10:41.117
You are the eldest,
and as such,

10:41.151 --> 10:44.017
I think you'll understand
why it had to be you.

10:44.050 --> 10:48.151
The answer lies buried
near your fort.

10:48.184 --> 10:50.750
I must be vague
in case of prying eyes,

10:50.783 --> 10:52.717
but above all things...

10:54.451 --> 10:57.251
the truth...

10:57.284 --> 10:59.783
must stay buried.

11:02.117 --> 11:04.783
Deepest apologies.

11:04.817 --> 11:05.850
Dad.

11:33.151 --> 11:36.351
Come on, Ted, how many
years have we know each other?

11:36.384 --> 11:41.884
There is absolutely no truth
whatsoever in the Post article.

11:41.917 --> 11:47.750
Look, my family has always
supported you in the...

11:47.783 --> 11:49.217
Lauren, wait!

11:49.251 --> 11:52.984
Wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait.

11:53.017 --> 11:54.351
Wait.

11:55.484 --> 11:56.783
Are you okay?

11:56.817 --> 11:58.884
What else would I expect?

11:58.917 --> 12:00.184
Do you wanna talk about it?

12:00.217 --> 12:02.017
No, I just...

12:02.050 --> 12:04.351
I just want a moment
by myself.

12:12.417 --> 12:14.151
I'm fine.

12:17.017 --> 12:18.618
I'm fine.

12:50.850 --> 12:52.783
You look
very pretty today.

12:53.850 --> 12:54.817
Two sugar cubes?

12:57.184 --> 12:59.184
Lauren!
This is off-limits.

15:17.950 --> 15:19.184
Jesus!

16:24.850 --> 16:27.384
Okay, okay.

16:56.084 --> 16:58.683
911, what's your emergency?

16:58.717 --> 17:01.084
Hello, hello?

17:10.950 --> 17:12.750
Hello?

17:12.782 --> 17:13.983
Ma'am, we just received a call
from this number.

17:14.017 --> 17:15.251
Is everything all right?

17:15.284 --> 17:17.251
Yeah, sorry, um...

17:17.284 --> 17:20.217
My daughter was playing
with my phone, so...

17:20.251 --> 17:22.782
I won't let it happen again.
I promise.

17:22.817 --> 17:24.884
Okay, ma'am, please be
more careful in the future.

17:27.950 --> 17:29.284
- Hey.
- Hi.

17:29.317 --> 17:31.017
Listen, I don't know
why Dad did that.

17:31.050 --> 17:32.683
Sure you do.

17:32.717 --> 17:34.151
What's wrong with you?
You look awful.

17:34.184 --> 17:35.917
Just got a little queasy
on my walk.

17:35.950 --> 17:37.817
Okay.

17:39.717 --> 17:41.284
Let's split it.

17:41.317 --> 17:45.950
I really, really don't care,
Will, okay? Seriously.

17:45.984 --> 17:48.184
Use it for your campaign
or something.

17:48.217 --> 17:49.750
I hope I still have your vote.

17:49.783 --> 17:51.117
Well, that depends
on your policies.

17:55.484 --> 17:57.217
Weren't you supposed
to be gone already?

17:57.251 --> 17:59.950
Yeah, actually,
but you try pulling Mom away

17:59.984 --> 18:01.417
from her favorite granddaughter.

18:01.451 --> 18:02.950
Lose a hand.

18:21.184 --> 18:22.184
Oh.

18:31.317 --> 18:35.384
We built a beautiful life
together, didn't we?

18:43.917 --> 18:44.850
What's wrong?

18:48.151 --> 18:50.984
It's everything, honestly.

18:51.017 --> 18:53.151
Your father was proud of you.

18:53.184 --> 18:57.184
Even when he didn't show it,
he was proud of you.

19:00.717 --> 19:02.683
I know there's gonna be
blood in the water,

19:02.717 --> 19:04.750
and the press
are gonna be digging,

19:04.783 --> 19:07.817
pointing their spotlight
on all of us.

19:09.451 --> 19:11.317
Are there any old enemies
of Dad's

19:11.351 --> 19:13.050
that I should be aware of?

19:15.050 --> 19:18.351
We both know he was no saint,

19:18.384 --> 19:21.050
but that is not
your burden to carry.

19:21.084 --> 19:22.384
It's mine.

19:22.417 --> 19:26.184
Well, I should know.
Maybe I can help.

19:26.217 --> 19:28.017
You wanna help?

19:28.050 --> 19:30.050
Crucify Reindorff.

19:30.084 --> 19:31.984
Win that case

19:32.017 --> 19:34.917
and help your family
win reelection.

19:47.284 --> 19:49.783
Good night, Claire-Bear.
I love you.

19:49.817 --> 19:52.017
I love you too, Mama.

20:00.384 --> 20:01.850
Sure you don't
want us to stay?

20:01.884 --> 20:04.050
No. I just need some time
to think.

20:04.084 --> 20:05.817
But I'll see you guys
tomorrow night.

20:05.850 --> 20:07.251
- I love you.
- Love you.

20:47.084 --> 20:48.451
All finest schools,

20:48.484 --> 20:50.251
the most prestigious firms
require...

20:50.284 --> 20:52.151
I don't want to represent
your rich friends!

20:52.184 --> 20:54.117
Why is that so wrong?

20:54.151 --> 20:56.284
You are throwing it all
away to be a civil servant,

20:56.317 --> 20:57.451
just like your boyfriend.

20:57.484 --> 20:59.417
FiancÃ©.

20:59.451 --> 21:01.683
Okay, that's enough!

21:01.717 --> 21:04.017
- Both of you.
- Talk to your daughter.

21:04.050 --> 21:05.384
You're acting
like this is

21:05.417 --> 21:07.451
some kind of prison sentence.

21:07.484 --> 21:09.317
It is.

22:21.117 --> 22:22.184
Hey.

22:25.984 --> 22:27.683
Can you hear me?

22:35.351 --> 22:36.750
Hey!

23:05.984 --> 23:07.417
Oh, shit!

23:07.451 --> 23:08.817
Shit.

23:10.184 --> 23:11.284
Shit.

23:37.917 --> 23:40.151
Nice mask.

23:41.217 --> 23:42.950
Who are you?

23:50.917 --> 23:53.017
I like masks.

23:53.050 --> 23:55.783
Answer the question.

23:58.251 --> 23:59.251
Where's Archer?

24:01.117 --> 24:03.084
Tell me your name.

24:07.217 --> 24:08.817
John.

24:08.850 --> 24:10.151
John what?

24:10.184 --> 24:12.417
Doe.

24:12.451 --> 24:14.950
You think this is a game?

24:14.984 --> 24:17.717
You're chained up in a bunker,
and I wanna know why.

24:24.950 --> 24:30.817
Show me your face,
Lauren Elizabeth Monroe.

24:33.017 --> 24:39.817
You want answers?
Look me in the eye and ask.

24:42.817 --> 24:45.251
Born November 7th, 1989.

24:45.284 --> 24:47.151
You have a younger brother,
William.

24:47.184 --> 24:50.717
As DA, you advocate for
the innocent and downtrodden

24:50.750 --> 24:53.417
to appease your conscience
for being born into wealth

24:53.451 --> 24:56.884
and because you knew
your father would disapprove.

24:56.917 --> 24:58.884
You used to bite
your nails incessantly,

24:58.917 --> 25:01.084
unless, of course,
you've kicked that habit.

25:01.117 --> 25:04.284
You have a daughter, Claire,
a husband, Scott,

25:04.317 --> 25:06.717
who you married against
your father's wishes.

25:06.750 --> 25:08.117
Should I continue,

25:08.151 --> 25:11.384
or will you take off
that ridiculous mask?

25:33.050 --> 25:35.017
It's good to finally meet you.

25:35.050 --> 25:36.417
Who are you?

25:38.217 --> 25:40.284
I'd like to think
I'm a member of the family

25:40.317 --> 25:41.750
after all these years.

25:41.783 --> 25:43.251
What do you mean, years?

25:43.284 --> 25:45.117
Exactly that.

25:46.850 --> 25:48.217
Years.

26:02.184 --> 26:06.783
So tell me,
what happened to your dad?

26:09.850 --> 26:11.017
Oh.

26:15.251 --> 26:17.184
How'd he die?

26:20.750 --> 26:23.417
My condolences.

26:27.917 --> 26:32.451
So he left me to you.

26:39.151 --> 26:41.117
That's quite the inheritance.

26:41.151 --> 26:43.151
So explain yourself.

26:43.184 --> 26:46.017
A man in your position,
only bad things come to mind.

26:46.050 --> 26:48.251
Are you good, Lauren?

26:48.284 --> 26:49.351
Who else knows you're here?

26:49.384 --> 26:50.783
Answer the question.

26:50.817 --> 26:51.884
Are you a good person?

26:51.917 --> 26:53.817
I'd like to think so.

26:53.850 --> 26:56.417
Then let me go.

26:56.451 --> 26:58.217
It's what a good person
would do.

26:58.251 --> 27:00.351
You know it's not that simple.

27:00.384 --> 27:03.017
You got a lot to lose.

27:03.050 --> 27:05.351
I have already lost everything.

27:05.384 --> 27:06.917
I need to know why you're here.

27:06.950 --> 27:08.950
Your needs?

27:08.984 --> 27:10.151
Your needs?

27:10.184 --> 27:13.084
You wanna know my name?

27:13.117 --> 27:16.017
You want the truth?

27:16.050 --> 27:21.417
Well, I want the juiciest steak
on God's green Earth.

27:21.451 --> 27:23.683
Rare.

27:23.717 --> 27:26.817
Baked potato, all the fixings.

27:26.850 --> 27:30.717
I want a Caesar salad,
bread and butter,

27:30.750 --> 27:33.184
packet of Gauloises cigarettes,

27:33.217 --> 27:34.451
some chocolate,

27:34.484 --> 27:36.451
a newspaper,

27:36.484 --> 27:38.683
and a 30-year-old
bottle of scotch,

27:38.717 --> 27:42.384
aged for every year
of my captivity.

27:45.417 --> 27:47.783
You give me what I asked for,

27:47.817 --> 27:49.451
and I will tell you everything.

27:49.484 --> 27:51.284
I need answers.

27:51.317 --> 27:54.750
And I need a steak.

27:54.783 --> 27:57.151
And while we're at it,
I want a shave.

27:57.184 --> 28:01.151
I wanna feel more like
a human being again.

28:01.184 --> 28:05.050
Now, we both know your
conscience, though pained,

28:05.084 --> 28:08.351
is not gonna just
let me go, not yet.

28:08.384 --> 28:12.817
But when all is said and done,
you will know the truth,

28:12.850 --> 28:16.050
and you will set me free.

28:16.084 --> 28:19.750
You're really gonna
play it that way?

28:21.151 --> 28:23.817
Look around.
You're the one in chains.

28:23.850 --> 28:25.384
I could just let you
rot in here,

28:25.417 --> 28:27.750
close the door
and walk away.

28:30.284 --> 28:33.184
But you won't.

28:33.217 --> 28:36.850
You really wanna risk that
for a steak?

28:36.884 --> 28:37.850
Wait.

28:45.884 --> 28:50.950
I'd also really like
a slice of key lime pie.

28:50.984 --> 28:54.084
And I would appreciate
that shave.

29:13.850 --> 29:17.317
C-Can I have the light
a little longer?

29:17.351 --> 29:22.783
Your father would only leave it
on an hour or so after he left.

29:38.917 --> 29:42.084
This is Detective
Emilio Sanchez, 75th Precinct.

29:42.117 --> 29:43.717
Leave me a message
and I'll come back to you

29:43.750 --> 29:45.017
as soon as I can.

29:45.050 --> 29:46.750
Sanchez, hey, it's me.

29:46.783 --> 29:48.850
I just emailed you
a set of prints

29:48.884 --> 29:51.417
I need you to get
into the system ASAP.

29:51.451 --> 29:53.417
Call me on my cell. Bye.

30:16.284 --> 30:18.451
Hey, honey. Sorry.

30:18.484 --> 30:20.451
Couldn't connect to you
for some reason.

30:20.484 --> 30:22.184
Hey.

30:22.217 --> 30:23.917
How was last night?

30:23.950 --> 30:25.917
Good, yeah.
I was just going through

30:25.950 --> 30:27.284
some of Dad's old things.

30:27.317 --> 30:28.717
You wanna talk about it?

30:28.750 --> 30:30.251
Maybe tonight.

30:30.284 --> 30:32.351
I'm actually headed
into court right now, so...

30:32.384 --> 30:33.351
Already here.

30:33.384 --> 30:34.717
Don't forget.

30:34.750 --> 30:35.984
Claire's recital
this afternoon.

30:36.017 --> 30:37.417
Yeah, okay.

30:37.451 --> 30:39.750
Well, I love you.

30:39.783 --> 30:40.817
Love you.

30:40.850 --> 30:42.984
Bye.

31:15.451 --> 31:18.683
Ohh...

31:18.717 --> 31:21.984
God help me if that isn't the
finest thing I've ever smelled.

31:22.017 --> 31:24.950
I brought you your food,
so let's talk.

31:24.984 --> 31:26.984
And talk we will.

31:27.017 --> 31:28.217
But first...

31:39.317 --> 31:43.084
Mmm!

31:45.351 --> 31:46.317
Mmm.

31:49.117 --> 31:52.184
You can't imagine
what this means to me.

31:52.217 --> 31:54.717
Thank you.

31:54.750 --> 31:57.251
What happened between
you and my dad?

32:00.217 --> 32:03.084
You're not like him.

32:03.117 --> 32:05.717
I suspect you're better
than he ever was.

32:05.750 --> 32:08.750
You've been deflecting my
questions ever since I got here.

32:08.783 --> 32:11.750
How's Catherine taking this?

32:11.783 --> 32:15.317
She was always
such a beautiful woman.

32:15.351 --> 32:17.317
My family is off-limits.

32:19.950 --> 32:22.850
A lawyer, a banker,
and a politician.

32:22.884 --> 32:25.251
The unholy trinity.

32:25.284 --> 32:26.817
Quite the family.

32:35.984 --> 32:37.984
When I get back,

32:38.017 --> 32:39.984
you're going
to tell me the truth,

32:40.017 --> 32:41.950
or it's the last time
you'll see me.

32:53.950 --> 32:55.184
Lauren, where the hell are you?

32:55.217 --> 32:56.750
Eddie, I'm gonna be
late for court.

32:56.783 --> 32:58.184
I'm sorry, but of
all the days to be late?

32:58.217 --> 32:59.351
Yeah, I know.

32:59.384 --> 33:00.817
Look, I need you
to run the trial.

33:00.850 --> 33:03.084
Haeven is gonna eat me alive.

33:03.117 --> 33:04.783
You're going to be fine.

33:04.817 --> 33:06.750
And don't let Robert
toss the SEC filing on...

33:06.783 --> 33:08.683
I know about the SEC filings.

33:08.717 --> 33:11.384
- I'll be there soon.
- Lauren, Lauren...

