Forgive me. I just...

34:09.284 --> 34:12.251
Once a year, Christmas,

34:12.284 --> 34:15.783
your father would
bring me chocolate.

34:15.817 --> 34:21.050
Not a whole bar,
just a little tiny square.

34:21.083 --> 34:23.850
It was my one treat
for the year,

34:23.884 --> 34:26.984
then he'd put it up there
for the rest of the year

34:27.016 --> 34:28.150
to taunt me,

34:28.184 --> 34:30.817
along with the pictures he took.

34:30.850 --> 34:31.817
Pictures?

34:31.850 --> 34:33.117
In the cigar box.

35:06.750 --> 35:08.317
What is this?

35:08.351 --> 35:10.084
It's my life.

35:15.384 --> 35:16.783
You, uh...

35:16.817 --> 35:19.084
You want some?

35:19.117 --> 35:20.750
It's all yours.

35:27.351 --> 35:30.351
My name is Morgan.
Morgan Warner.

35:43.284 --> 35:45.050
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

35:45.084 --> 35:49.717
It's been a long time
since I had any human contact.

35:49.750 --> 35:53.217
You know, just to touch
someone's skin.

36:12.217 --> 36:14.850
I used to smoke Gauloises
cigarettes back in the day.

36:16.417 --> 36:18.251
It was a habit I picked up

36:18.284 --> 36:21.251
because I thought it would
make me appear more refined.

36:22.884 --> 36:25.184
Get to the point.

36:27.217 --> 36:30.817
I was a foolish young man
when I met your father.

36:30.850 --> 36:34.783
We had similar vices.

36:34.817 --> 36:38.050
Gambling, ego, women.

36:38.084 --> 36:40.917
That was the greatest time
of my life.

36:40.950 --> 36:43.284
We became partners.

36:43.317 --> 36:47.117
Archer was fearless,
but he couldn't read people.

36:47.151 --> 36:49.117
He was so young and careless
back then.

36:49.151 --> 36:51.384
So you helped him
become a card shark?

36:51.417 --> 36:53.417
Oh, no, he was already a shark.

36:53.451 --> 36:56.451
I just provided an edge.

36:56.484 --> 36:59.184
If there's one thing
your father wanted

36:59.217 --> 37:02.817
in business, cards, politics,

37:02.850 --> 37:04.117
it was an edge.

37:04.151 --> 37:06.151
What happened between you?

37:09.151 --> 37:11.384
I was gonna become a doctor.

37:14.084 --> 37:17.151
I could've done so much
with my life.

37:19.050 --> 37:20.984
- That night...
- What happened?

37:26.317 --> 37:30.284
We'd had a few drinks
before leaving the summer house

37:30.317 --> 37:33.317
for a big game in the city.

37:33.351 --> 37:35.317
We should never have been
on the road.

37:35.351 --> 37:37.417
I'll never forget that sound.

37:39.484 --> 37:41.084
It happened so fast.

37:43.384 --> 37:46.384
My heart was pounding like it
was gonna burst in my chest.

37:46.417 --> 37:49.017
And my mouth,
I could barely swallow,

37:49.050 --> 37:50.917
I was so scared.

37:53.484 --> 37:56.917
He was just a kid.

37:56.950 --> 37:58.884
He was like us.

38:01.284 --> 38:04.217
I figured the only thing
we could do was call the police

38:04.251 --> 38:06.917
and, you know, say
there had been an accident.

38:06.950 --> 38:08.683
But, uh, he panicked.

38:10.084 --> 38:11.817
He said we couldn't.

38:11.850 --> 38:14.184
He said the cops would be
looking for his dented car.

38:14.217 --> 38:17.917
He said he'd go to jail,
that he'd lose everything.

38:17.950 --> 38:19.950
"If there's no body,
there's no crime.

38:19.984 --> 38:21.384
If there's no body,
there's no crime."

38:21.417 --> 38:23.783
He kept saying it
over and over again.

38:23.817 --> 38:27.050
"If there's no body,
there's no crime."

38:27.084 --> 38:29.750
I-I tried to do
the right thing.

38:29.783 --> 38:31.184
My dad killed a man?

38:31.217 --> 38:33.783
It was an accident.

38:35.917 --> 38:38.317
But paranoia infected him.

38:38.351 --> 38:40.184
What happened to the body?

38:41.384 --> 38:42.717
We buried it.

38:45.017 --> 38:46.750
That is to say,
your father buried it.

38:46.783 --> 38:49.117
I wanted no part of it.

38:49.151 --> 38:52.217
I wasn't about to cover up
a homicide.

38:52.251 --> 38:54.917
You know, I mean,
an accident is one thing, but...

38:57.117 --> 38:58.384
Maybe I should have.

39:00.817 --> 39:02.917
Maybe I'd still have a life.

39:02.950 --> 39:04.317
Morgan!

39:04.351 --> 39:05.783
Who was he?

39:05.817 --> 39:07.184
I don't know.

39:08.750 --> 39:10.184
You buried a body

39:10.217 --> 39:12.351
and didn't even bother
to find out who it was?

39:12.384 --> 39:17.117
I had slightly more pressing
matters at hand.

39:17.151 --> 39:19.251
What would you have done?

39:19.284 --> 39:21.251
Would you have buried him
and walked away,

39:21.284 --> 39:23.750
or would you have made the call
to the police?

39:23.783 --> 39:25.950
I'd like to think
I'd make the call.

39:25.984 --> 39:28.950
Well, then you would
be here like me.

39:28.984 --> 39:32.817
- Why go to all this trouble?
- Why not just kill me?

39:34.084 --> 39:36.284
I begged him to.

39:36.317 --> 39:38.984
Days turned into weeks,
then months,

39:39.017 --> 39:41.117
then so much time had gone by,

39:41.151 --> 39:44.317
he couldn't bring himself
to let me go.

39:44.351 --> 39:47.151
He was scared
I'd turn him in.

39:49.884 --> 39:51.917
I wouldn't have said a word.

39:51.950 --> 39:54.717
Not a word...

39:54.750 --> 39:57.850
if it'd have bought me
my freedom.

39:57.884 --> 39:59.850
If Archer had a conscience,

39:59.884 --> 40:03.017
he would've just
put me out of my misery.

40:03.050 --> 40:07.084
Instead, he offered me
the chance to kill myself.

40:10.117 --> 40:15.084
But no matter the agony,
the hopelessness,

40:15.117 --> 40:18.217
my life had meaning.

40:18.251 --> 40:21.184
My survival
would be my revenge.

40:21.217 --> 40:23.251
But people must have
missed you,

40:23.284 --> 40:25.351
looked for you.

40:27.050 --> 40:30.351
He said I stole his winnings,
left the country.

40:30.384 --> 40:32.984
How do I know that
you're telling me the truth?

40:33.017 --> 40:35.384
It's not like my dad's here
to defend himself.

40:37.351 --> 40:39.984
I said your father
had three vices.

40:40.017 --> 40:42.050
Poker, obviously,

40:42.084 --> 40:44.850
ego, of course,

40:44.884 --> 40:48.251
but we haven't even begun
to discuss the women.

40:48.284 --> 40:49.917
One woman in particular.

40:49.950 --> 40:51.717
What does it have
to do with anything?

40:51.750 --> 40:54.217
You said you could
handle the truth.

40:56.884 --> 41:01.017
Archer loved your mother,
but, uh, Sofia...

41:02.850 --> 41:06.417
she was everything
your mother was not.

41:06.451 --> 41:08.717
Uncomplicated,

41:08.750 --> 41:09.884
unrestrained,

41:09.917 --> 41:12.750
free from conformity.

41:12.783 --> 41:14.950
Sofia wasn't an affair.

41:14.984 --> 41:16.750
She was an obsession,

41:16.783 --> 41:21.184
providing for Archer's
darker appetites.

41:21.217 --> 41:24.251
He used to call her
his Gypsy Rose.

41:25.884 --> 41:27.850
You must have had
some kind of inclination...

41:27.884 --> 41:29.351
I don't believe you.

41:29.384 --> 41:33.317
Why not?
Since the world has turned,

41:33.351 --> 41:35.151
powerful men
have kept mistresses,

41:35.184 --> 41:37.451
and he kept her
till his dying day.

41:37.484 --> 41:39.117
He wouldn't do that to my mom.

41:39.151 --> 41:41.984
Does any daughter
really know her father?

41:43.384 --> 41:45.084
You're lying.

41:45.117 --> 41:47.884
I don't expect you
to take my word for it, okay?

41:47.917 --> 41:50.217
- Why don't you go check?
- How?

41:50.251 --> 41:52.217
He used to visit her
every Tuesday,

41:52.251 --> 41:53.817
72nd and Parkway.

41:53.850 --> 41:56.783
- Her name is Sofia Fiore.
- Bullshit.

41:56.817 --> 41:58.984
If you don't believe me,
go ask Harold.

41:59.017 --> 42:02.750
I'm sure he kept an entirely
separate inheritance for her.

42:02.783 --> 42:07.017
- She was the love of his life.
- Shut the hell up!

42:07.050 --> 42:09.151
If you're lying,

42:09.184 --> 42:11.783
I swear you'll
never see me again.

42:11.817 --> 42:13.251
What if I'm not?

42:53.484 --> 42:55.884
Can you check to see if
there were any missing persons

42:55.917 --> 42:58.117
named Morgan Warner
during the late '80s?

42:58.151 --> 43:00.717
Morgan Warner.
Yeah, okay.

43:00.750 --> 43:02.050
What's it for?

43:02.084 --> 43:04.050
My dad left him something
in his will,

43:04.084 --> 43:06.084
and I'm trying to find out
what happened to him.

43:06.117 --> 43:08.084
No emails.
Just forward whatever you find

43:08.117 --> 43:10.084
on to my parent's
summer house.

43:10.117 --> 43:11.750
All right.

43:35.117 --> 43:37.384
Well, I'm glad you decided
to join us, Ms. Monroe.

43:37.417 --> 43:39.151
May it please the court,

43:39.184 --> 43:41.050
I'd like to offer my sincere
apology to Your Honor

43:41.084 --> 43:43.984
and the ladies and gentlemen
of the jury.

43:52.284 --> 43:54.184
What did I miss?

43:54.217 --> 43:56.750
Besides the birth
of my 15 ulcers?

43:58.950 --> 44:00.351
Court is in session.

44:00.384 --> 44:03.984
Mr. Haeven,
please call your next witness.

